{
  "video_id": "9RTkZaX1cH0",
  "title": "What a planet needs to sustain life | Dave Brain",
  "es": 1,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12943.0,
      "end_time": 14363.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m really glad to be here."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 15150.0,
      "end_time": 16703.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m glad you&#39;re here,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 16727.0,
      "end_time": 18560.0,
      "text": "because that would be a little weird."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 19460.0,
      "end_time": 21565.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m glad we&#39;re all here."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 22303.0,
      "end_time": 25156.0,
      "text": "And by \"here,\" I don&#39;t mean here."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 26831.0,
      "end_time": 27980.0,
      "text": "Or here."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 28728.0,
      "end_time": 29880.0,
      "text": "But here."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 29904.0,
      "end_time": 31540.0,
      "text": "I mean Earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 31627.0,
      "end_time": 35570.0,
      "text": "And by \"we,\" I don&#39;t mean those of us in this auditorium,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 35594.0,
      "end_time": 37640.0,
      "text": "but life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 37880.0,
      "end_time": 38537.0,
      "text": "all life on Earth --"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 38561.0,
      "end_time": 43943.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 44280.0,
      "end_time": 46271.0,
      "text": "from complex to single-celled,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 46295.0,
      "end_time": 48619.0,
      "text": "from mold to mushrooms"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 48643.0,
      "end_time": 50210.0,
      "text": "to flying bears."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 50450.0,
      "end_time": 51411.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 53736.0,
      "end_time": 55245.0,
      "text": "The interesting thing is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 55269.0,
      "end_time": 58300.0,
      "text": "Earth is the only place we know of that has life --"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 58324.0,
      "end_time": 60201.0,
      "text": "8.7 million species."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 60660.0,
      "end_time": 61913.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ve looked other places,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 61938.0,
      "end_time": 64350.0,
      "text": "maybe not as hard as we should or we could,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 64590.0,
      "end_time": 65986.0,
      "text": "but we&#39;ve looked and haven&#39;t found any;"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 66100.0,
      "end_time": 68286.0,
      "text": "Earth is the only place we know of with life."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 69318.0,
      "end_time": 70592.0,
      "text": "Is Earth special?"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 71591.0,
      "end_time": 74440.0,
      "text": "This is a question I&#39;ve wanted to know the answer to"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 74690.0,
      "end_time": 75323.0,
      "text": "since I was a small child,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 75347.0,
      "end_time": 77378.0,
      "text": "and I suspect 80 percent of this auditorium"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 77403.0,
      "end_time": 80411.0,
      "text": "has thought the same thing and also wanted to know the answer."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 80879.0,
      "end_time": 83460.0,
      "text": "To understand whether there are any planets --"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 83700.0,
      "end_time": 85348.0,
      "text": "out there in our solar system or beyond --"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 85372.0,
      "end_time": 86830.0,
      "text": "that can support life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 86854.0,
      "end_time": 90510.0,
      "text": "the first step is to understand what life here requires."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 90575.0,
      "end_time": 94138.0,
      "text": "It turns out, of all of those 8.7 million species,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 94162.0,
      "end_time": 96360.0,
      "text": "life only needs three things."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 97320.0,
      "end_time": 99884.0,
      "text": "On one side, all life on Earth needs energy."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 99908.0,
      "end_time": 103393.0,
      "text": "Complex life like us derives our energy from the sun,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 103417.0,
      "end_time": 105518.0,
      "text": "but life deep underground can get its energy"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 105542.0,
      "end_time": 107264.0,
      "text": "from things like chemical reactions."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 107288.0,
      "end_time": 109439.0,
      "text": "There are a number of different energy sources"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 109463.0,
      "end_time": 110705.0,
      "text": "available on all planets."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 111400.0,
      "end_time": 112556.0,
      "text": "On the other side,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 112580.0,
      "end_time": 115285.0,
      "text": "all life needs food or nourishment."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 115741.0,
      "end_time": 120215.0,
      "text": "And this seems like a tall order, especially if you want a succulent tomato."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 120239.0,
      "end_time": 121955.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 121979.0,
      "end_time": 125450.0,
      "text": "However, all life on Earth derives its nourishment"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 125690.0,
      "end_time": 127990.0,
      "text": "from only six chemical elements,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 127123.0,
      "end_time": 130127.0,
      "text": "and these elements can be found on any planetary body"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 130151.00000000001,
      "end_time": 131487.0,
      "text": "in our solar system."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 132537.0,
      "end_time": 135764.0,
      "text": "So that leaves the thing in the middle as the tall pole,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 135788.0,
      "end_time": 137742.0,
      "text": "the thing that&#39;s hardest to achieve."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 137766.0,
      "end_time": 139658.0,
      "text": "Not moose, but water."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 139682.0,
      "end_time": 142463.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 143285.0,
      "end_time": 145790.0,
      "text": "Although moose would be pretty cool."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 145103.0,
      "end_time": 146261.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 146285.0,
      "end_time": 151820.0,
      "text": "And not frozen water, and not water in a gaseous state, but liquid water."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 152748.0,
      "end_time": 155201.0,
      "text": "This is what life needs to survive, all life."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 155680.0,
      "end_time": 159160.0,
      "text": "And many solar system bodies don&#39;t have liquid water,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 159400.0,
      "end_time": 160676.0,
      "text": "and so we don&#39;t look there."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 160700.0,
      "end_time": 163692.0,
      "text": "Other solar system bodies might have abundant liquid water,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 163717.0,
      "end_time": 165520.0,
      "text": "even more than Earth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 165760.0,
      "end_time": 167525.0,
      "text": "but it&#39;s trapped beneath an icy shell,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 167550.0,
      "end_time": 169811.0,
      "text": "and so it&#39;s hard to access, it&#39;s hard to get to,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 169835.0,
      "end_time": 172554.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s hard to even find out if there&#39;s any life there."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 173475.0,
      "end_time": 176470.0,
      "text": "So that leaves a few bodies that we should think about."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 176494.0,
      "end_time": 178923.0,
      "text": "So let&#39;s make the problem simpler for ourselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 178947.0,
      "end_time": 182288.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s think only about liquid water on the surface of a planet."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 182312.0,
      "end_time": 185268.0,
      "text": "There are only three bodies to think about in our solar system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 185292.0,
      "end_time": 187874.0,
      "text": "with regard to liquid water on the surface of a planet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 187898.0,
      "end_time": 192724.0,
      "text": "and in order of distance from the sun, it&#39;s: Venus, Earth and Mars."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 193265.0,
      "end_time": 196637.0,
      "text": "You want to have an atmosphere for water to be liquid."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 196661.0,
      "end_time": 199390.0,
      "text": "You have to be very careful with that atmosphere."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 199630.0,
      "end_time": 202475.0,
      "text": "You can&#39;t have too much atmosphere, too thick or too warm an atmosphere,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 202499.0,
      "end_time": 205404.0,
      "text": "because then you end up too hot like Venus,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 205428.0,
      "end_time": 207165.0,
      "text": "and you can&#39;t have liquid water."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 207189.0,
      "end_time": 211142.0,
      "text": "But if you have too little atmosphere and it&#39;s too thin and too cold,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 211166.0,
      "end_time": 213190.0,
      "text": "you end up like Mars, too cold."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 213865.0,
      "end_time": 216340.0,
      "text": "So Venus is too hot, Mars is too cold,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 216364.0,
      "end_time": 217528.0,
      "text": "and Earth is just right."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 217552.0,
      "end_time": 221270.0,
      "text": "You can look at these images behind me and you can see automatically"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 221510.0,
      "end_time": 223648.0,
      "text": "where life can survive in our solar system."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 224296.0,
      "end_time": 225896.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a Goldilocks-type problem,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 225920.0,
      "end_time": 228410.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s so simple that a child could understand it."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 229452.0,
      "end_time": 230632.0,
      "text": "However,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 231450.0,
      "end_time": 234378.0,
      "text": "I&#39;d like to remind you of two things"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 234402.0,
      "end_time": 237356.0,
      "text": "from the Goldilocks story that we may not think about so often"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 237380.0,
      "end_time": 239476.0,
      "text": "but that I think are really relevant here."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 240560.0,
      "end_time": 241206.0,
      "text": "Number one:"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 242311.0,
      "end_time": 245103.0,
      "text": "if Mama Bear&#39;s bowl is too cold"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 245833.0,
      "end_time": 247841.0,
      "text": "when Goldilocks walks into the room,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 248642.0,
      "end_time": 250785.0,
      "text": "does that mean it&#39;s always been too cold?"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 251825.0,
      "end_time": 255930.0,
      "text": "Or could it have been just right at some other time?"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 255650.0,
      "end_time": 259331.0,
      "text": "When Goldilocks walks into the room determines the answer"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 259355.00000000003,
      "end_time": 260687.00000000003,
      "text": "that we get in the story."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 261113.0,
      "end_time": 262844.0,
      "text": "And the same is true with planets."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 262868.0,
      "end_time": 264894.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re not static things. They change."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 264918.0,
      "end_time": 266660.0,
      "text": "They vary. They evolve."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 266684.0,
      "end_time": 268727.0,
      "text": "And atmospheres do the same."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 268751.0,
      "end_time": 270453.0,
      "text": "So let me give you an example."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 270477.0,
      "end_time": 272479.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s one of my favorite pictures of Mars."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 272503.0,
      "end_time": 275633.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s not the highest resolution image, it&#39;s not the sexiest image,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 275658.0,
      "end_time": 277161.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s not the most recent image,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 277185.0,
      "end_time": 280679.0,
      "text": "but it&#39;s an image that shows riverbeds cut into the surface of the planet;"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 281320.0,
      "end_time": 283904.0,
      "text": "riverbeds carved by flowing, liquid water;"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 285515.0,
      "end_time": 290401.0,
      "text": "riverbeds that take hundreds or thousands or tens of thousands of years to form."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 290425.0,
      "end_time": 292430.0,
      "text": "This can&#39;t happen on Mars today."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 292670.0,
      "end_time": 294548.0,
      "text": "The atmosphere of Mars today is too thin and too cold"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 294572.0,
      "end_time": 296713.0,
      "text": "for water to be stable as a liquid."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 296737.0,
      "end_time": 301850.0,
      "text": "This one image tells you that the atmosphere of Mars changed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 301109.0,
      "end_time": 303140.0,
      "text": "and it changed in big ways."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 303714.0,
      "end_time": 308523.0,
      "text": "And it changed from a state that we would define as habitable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 308547.0,
      "end_time": 312137.0,
      "text": "because the three requirements for life were present long ago."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 313490.0,
      "end_time": 315116.0,
      "text": "Where did that atmosphere go"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 315141.0,
      "end_time": 317961.0,
      "text": "that allowed water to be liquid at the surface?"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 317985.0,
      "end_time": 321332.0,
      "text": "Well, one idea is it escaped away to space."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 321356.0,
      "end_time": 324220.0,
      "text": "Atmospheric particles got enough energy to break free"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 324470.0,
      "end_time": 325700.0,
      "text": "from the gravity of the planet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 325724.0,
      "end_time": 328413.0,
      "text": "escaping away to space, never to return."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 328437.0,
      "end_time": 331125.0,
      "text": "And this happens with all bodies with atmospheres."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 331149.0,
      "end_time": 332321.0,
      "text": "Comets have tails"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 332345.0,
      "end_time": 335602.0,
      "text": "that are incredibly visible reminders of atmospheric escape."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 335626.0,
      "end_time": 339340.0,
      "text": "But Venus also has an atmosphere that escapes with time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 339590.0,
      "end_time": 340719.0,
      "text": "and Mars and Earth as well."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 340743.0,
      "end_time": 343711.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s just a matter of degree and a matter of scale."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 344920.0,
      "end_time": 346768.0,
      "text": "So we&#39;d like to figure out how much escaped over time"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 346792.0,
      "end_time": 348907.0,
      "text": "so we can explain this transition."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 348932.0,
      "end_time": 351543.0,
      "text": "How do atmospheres get their energy for escape?"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 351567.0,
      "end_time": 353698.0,
      "text": "How do particles get enough energy to escape?"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 353722.0,
      "end_time": 356907.0,
      "text": "There are two ways, if we&#39;re going to reduce things a little bit."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 356931.0,
      "end_time": 358820.0,
      "text": "Number one, sunlight."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 358106.0,
      "end_time": 361518.0,
      "text": "Light emitted from the sun can be absorbed by atmospheric particles"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 361542.0,
      "end_time": 363256.0,
      "text": "and warm the particles."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 363280.0,
      "end_time": 365388.0,
      "text": "Yes, I&#39;m dancing, but they --"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 365412.0,
      "end_time": 366883.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 367693.0,
      "end_time": 369604.0,
      "text": "Oh my God, not even at my wedding."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 369629.0,
      "end_time": 371121.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 371145.0,
      "end_time": 374147.0,
      "text": "They get enough energy to escape and break free"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 374172.0,
      "end_time": 376672.0,
      "text": "from the gravity of the planet just by warming."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 376696.0,
      "end_time": 379858.0,
      "text": "A second way they can get energy is from the solar wind."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 379882.0,
      "end_time": 384908.0,
      "text": "These are particles, mass, material, spit out from the surface of the sun,"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 384932.0,
      "end_time": 387336.0,
      "text": "and they go screaming through the solar system"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 387360.0,
      "end_time": 389145.0,
      "text": "at 400 kilometers per second,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 389169.0,
      "end_time": 391763.0,
      "text": "sometimes faster during solar storms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 391787.0,
      "end_time": 394508.0,
      "text": "and they go hurtling through interplanetary space"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 394533.0,
      "end_time": 396979.0,
      "text": "towards planets and their atmospheres,"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 397300.0,
      "end_time": 398628.0,
      "text": "and they may provide energy"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 398652.0,
      "end_time": 400780.0,
      "text": "for atmospheric particles to escape as well."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 401182.0,
      "end_time": 403151.0,
      "text": "This is something that I&#39;m interested in,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 403175.0,
      "end_time": 404888.0,
      "text": "because it relates to habitability."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 405378.0,
      "end_time": 408510.0,
      "text": "I mentioned that there were two things about the Goldilocks story"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 408534.0,
      "end_time": 411518.0,
      "text": "that I wanted to bring to your attention and remind you about,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 411542.0,
      "end_time": 413780.0,
      "text": "and the second one is a little bit more subtle."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 413805.0,
      "end_time": 416593.0,
      "text": "If Papa Bear&#39;s bowl is too hot,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 418180.0,
      "end_time": 421414.0,
      "text": "and Mama Bear&#39;s bowl is too cold,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 423570.0,
      "end_time": 426168.0,
      "text": "shouldn&#39;t Baby Bear&#39;s bowl be even colder"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 427810.0,
      "end_time": 428877.0,
      "text": "if we&#39;re following the trend?"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 430195.0,
      "end_time": 432507.0,
      "text": "This thing that you&#39;ve accepted your entire life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 432531.0,
      "end_time": 435601.0,
      "text": "when you think about it a little bit more, may not be so simple."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 436513.0,
      "end_time": 440541.0,
      "text": "And of course, distance of a planet from the sun determines its temperature."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 440565.0,
      "end_time": 442831.0,
      "text": "This has to play into habitability."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 442855.0,
      "end_time": 445785.0,
      "text": "But maybe there are other things we should be thinking about."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 445809.0,
      "end_time": 447425.0,
      "text": "Maybe it&#39;s the bowls themselves"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 447449.0,
      "end_time": 450505.0,
      "text": "that are also helping to determine the outcome in the story,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 450529.0,
      "end_time": 451829.0,
      "text": "what is just right."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 452765.0,
      "end_time": 455630.0,
      "text": "I could talk to you about a lot of different characteristics"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 455654.0,
      "end_time": 456805.0,
      "text": "of these three planets"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 456829.0,
      "end_time": 458398.0,
      "text": "that may influence habitability,"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 458422.0,
      "end_time": 461160.0,
      "text": "but for selfish reasons related to my own research"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 461400.0,
      "end_time": 464628.0,
      "text": "and the fact that I&#39;m standing up here holding the clicker and you&#39;re not --"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 464652.0,
      "end_time": 465657.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 465682.0,
      "end_time": 467791.0,
      "text": "I would like to talk for just a minute or two"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 467815.0,
      "end_time": 469112.0,
      "text": "about magnetic fields."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 469715.0,
      "end_time": 472246.0,
      "text": "Earth has one; Venus and Mars do not."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 472825.0,
      "end_time": 475948.0,
      "text": "Magnetic fields are generated in the deep interior of a planet"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 475972.0,
      "end_time": 479688.0,
      "text": "by electrically conducting churning fluid material"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 479713.0,
      "end_time": 482618.0,
      "text": "that creates this big old magnetic field that surrounds Earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 482642.0,
      "end_time": 485380.0,
      "text": "If you have a compass, you know which way north is."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 485620.0,
      "end_time": 486556.0,
      "text": "Venus and Mars don&#39;t have that."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 486580.0,
      "end_time": 488494.0,
      "text": "If you have a compass on Venus and Mars,"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 488518.0,
      "end_time": 489914.0,
      "text": "congratulations, you&#39;re lost."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 489938.0,
      "end_time": 491841.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 491865.0,
      "end_time": 493905.0,
      "text": "Does this influence habitability?"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 495175.0,
      "end_time": 496477.0,
      "text": "Well, how might it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 497240.0,
      "end_time": 499628.0,
      "text": "Many scientists think that a magnetic field of a planet"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 499652.0,
      "end_time": 502460.0,
      "text": "serves as a shield for the atmosphere,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 502710.0,
      "end_time": 505426.0,
      "text": "deflecting solar wind particles around the planet"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 505450.0,
      "end_time": 507265.0,
      "text": "in a bit of a force field-type effect"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 507289.0,
      "end_time": 509989.0,
      "text": "having to do with electric charge of those particles."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 510362.0,
      "end_time": 513989.0,
      "text": "I like to think of it instead as a salad bar sneeze guard for planets."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 514130.0,
      "end_time": 516292.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 516962.0,
      "end_time": 520342.0,
      "text": "And yes, my colleagues who watch this later will realize"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 520366.0,
      "end_time": 522910.0,
      "text": "this is the first time in the history of our community"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 522933.99999999994,
      "end_time": 525214.0,
      "text": "that the solar wind has been equated with mucus."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 525238.0,
      "end_time": 526888.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 528978.0,
      "end_time": 532453.0,
      "text": "OK, so the effect, then, is that Earth may have been protected"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 532477.0,
      "end_time": 533646.0,
      "text": "for billions of years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 533670.0,
      "end_time": 535520.0,
      "text": "because we&#39;ve had a magnetic field."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 535544.0,
      "end_time": 537723.0,
      "text": "Atmosphere hasn&#39;t been able to escape."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 537747.0,
      "end_time": 539853.0,
      "text": "Mars, on the other hand, has been unprotected"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 539878.0,
      "end_time": 541720.0,
      "text": "because of its lack of magnetic field,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 541744.0,
      "end_time": 543696.0,
      "text": "and over billions of years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 543720.0,
      "end_time": 545900.0,
      "text": "maybe enough atmosphere has been stripped away"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 545924.0,
      "end_time": 548516.0,
      "text": "to account for a transition from a habitable planet"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 548541.0,
      "end_time": 550207.0,
      "text": "to the planet that we see today."
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 551590.0,
      "end_time": 554480.0,
      "text": "Other scientists think that magnetic fields"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 554720.0,
      "end_time": 556235.0,
      "text": "may act more like the sails on a ship,"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 556958.0,
      "end_time": 561995.0,
      "text": "enabling the planet to interact with more energy from the solar wind"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 562190.0,
      "end_time": 565291.0,
      "text": "than the planet would have been able to interact with by itself."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 565315.0,
      "end_time": 567806.0,
      "text": "The sails may gather energy from the solar wind."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 567830.0,
      "end_time": 570496.0,
      "text": "The magnetic field may gather energy from the solar wind"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 570520.0,
      "end_time": 573764.0,
      "text": "that allows even more atmospheric escape to happen."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 573788.0,
      "end_time": 576420.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s an idea that has to be tested,"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 576660.0,
      "end_time": 577951.0,
      "text": "but the effect and how it works"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 577975.0,
      "end_time": 579126.0,
      "text": "seems apparent."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 579150.0,
      "end_time": 580300.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s because we know"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 580325.0,
      "end_time": 583400.0,
      "text": "energy from the solar wind is being deposited into our atmosphere"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 583424.0,
      "end_time": 584574.0,
      "text": "here on Earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 584599.0,
      "end_time": 587400.0,
      "text": "That energy is conducted along magnetic field lines"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 587280.0,
      "end_time": 588376.0,
      "text": "down into the polar regions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 588400.0,
      "end_time": 590536.0,
      "text": "resulting in incredibly beautiful aurora."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 590560.0,
      "end_time": 593215.0,
      "text": "If you&#39;ve ever experienced them, it&#39;s magnificent."
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 593240.0,
      "end_time": 595246.0,
      "text": "We know the energy is getting in."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 595270.0,
      "end_time": 598303.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re trying to measure how many particles are getting out"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 598327.0,
      "end_time": 601365.0,
      "text": "and if the magnetic field is influencing this in any way."
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 602722.0,
      "end_time": 605102.0,
      "text": "So I&#39;ve posed a problem for you here,"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 605126.0,
      "end_time": 606672.0,
      "text": "but I don&#39;t have a solution yet."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 606696.0,
      "end_time": 607972.0,
      "text": "We don&#39;t have a solution."
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 608702.0,
      "end_time": 611590.0,
      "text": "But we&#39;re working on it. How are we working on it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 611830.0,
      "end_time": 613381.0,
      "text": "Well, we&#39;ve sent spacecraft to all three planets."
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 613405.0,
      "end_time": 614881.0,
      "text": "Some of them are orbiting now,"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 614905.0,
      "end_time": 617977.0,
      "text": "including the MAVEN spacecraft which is currently orbiting Mars,"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 618100.0,
      "end_time": 621533.0,
      "text": "which I&#39;m involved with and which is led here,"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 621557.0,
      "end_time": 623366.0,
      "text": "out of the University of Colorado."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 623390.0,
      "end_time": 625672.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s designed to measure atmospheric escape."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 626220.0,
      "end_time": 628496.0,
      "text": "We have similar measurements from Venus and Earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 628953.0,
      "end_time": 630617.0,
      "text": "Once we have all our measurements,"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 630642.0,
      "end_time": 633517.0,
      "text": "we can combine all these together, and we can understand"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 633541.0,
      "end_time": 636958.0,
      "text": "how all three planets interact with their space environment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 636982.0,
      "end_time": 638144.0,
      "text": "with the surroundings."
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 638168.0,
      "end_time": 641690.0,
      "text": "And we can decide whether magnetic fields are important for habitability"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 641714.0,
      "end_time": 642872.0,
      "text": "or not."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 642896.0,
      "end_time": 645161.0,
      "text": "Once we have that answer, why should you care?"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 645185.0,
      "end_time": 646484.0,
      "text": "I mean, I care deeply ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 648128.0,
      "end_time": 650134.0,
      "text": "And financially as well, but deeply."
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 650158.0,
      "end_time": 652000.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 652763.0,
      "end_time": 654681.0,
      "text": "First of all, an answer to this question"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 654705.0,
      "end_time": 656808.0,
      "text": "will teach us more about these three planets,"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 656832.0,
      "end_time": 657992.0,
      "text": "Venus, Earth and Mars,"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 658160.0,
      "end_time": 660926.0,
      "text": "not only about how they interact with their environment today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 660951.0,
      "end_time": 662878.0,
      "text": "but how they were billions of years ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 662902.0,
      "end_time": 664964.0,
      "text": "whether they were habitable long ago or not."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 664988.0,
      "end_time": 666632.0,
      "text": "It will teach us about atmospheres"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 666656.0,
      "end_time": 668651.0,
      "text": "that surround us and that are close."
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 669127.0,
      "end_time": 671310.0,
      "text": "But moreover, what we learn from these planets"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 671335.0,
      "end_time": 673356.0,
      "text": "can be applied to atmospheres everywhere,"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 674485.0,
      "end_time": 677398.0,
      "text": "including planets that we&#39;re now observing around other stars."
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 677422.0,
      "end_time": 679177.0,
      "text": "For example, the Kepler spacecraft,"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 679201.0,
      "end_time": 682409.0,
      "text": "which is built and controlled here in Boulder,"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 682433.0,
      "end_time": 685718.0,
      "text": "has been observing a postage stamp-sized region of the sky"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 685742.0,
      "end_time": 686988.0,
      "text": "for a couple years now,"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 687130.0,
      "end_time": 689241.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s found thousands of planets --"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 689265.0,
      "end_time": 692178.0,
      "text": "in one postage stamp-sized region of the sky"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 692202.0,
      "end_time": 696291.0,
      "text": "that we don&#39;t think is any different from any other part of the sky."
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 696815.0,
      "end_time": 698625.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ve gone, in 20 years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 698649.0,
      "end_time": 702686.0,
      "text": "from knowing of zero planets outside of our solar system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 702710.0,
      "end_time": 704463.0,
      "text": "to now having so many,"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 704487.0,
      "end_time": 707626.0,
      "text": "that we don&#39;t know which ones to investigate first."
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 709269.0,
      "end_time": 710729.0,
      "text": "Any lever will help."
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 712539.0,
      "end_time": 716122.0,
      "text": "In fact, based on observations that Kepler&#39;s taken"
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 716147.0,
      "end_time": 718276.0,
      "text": "and other similar observations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 718300.0,
      "end_time": 719468.0,
      "text": "we now believe that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 719493.0,
      "end_time": 724192.0,
      "text": "of the 200 billion stars in the Milky Way galaxy alone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 724786.0,
      "end_time": 729390.0,
      "text": "on average, every star has at least one planet."
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 730819.0,
      "end_time": 732322.0,
      "text": "In addition to that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 732346.0,
      "end_time": 738470.0,
      "text": "estimates suggest there are somewhere between 40 billion and 100 billion"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 738710.0,
      "end_time": 741403.0,
      "text": "of those planets that we would define as habitable"
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 743139.0,
      "end_time": 744551.0,
      "text": "in just our galaxy."
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 746590.0,
      "end_time": 748627.0,
      "text": "We have the observations of those planets,"
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 748651.0,
      "end_time": 751135.0,
      "text": "but we just don&#39;t know which ones are habitable yet."
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 751159.0,
      "end_time": 754765.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a little bit like being trapped on a red spot --"
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 754789.0,
      "end_time": 755960.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 755984.0,
      "end_time": 757216.0,
      "text": "on a stage"
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 758178.0,
      "end_time": 761740.0,
      "text": "and knowing that there are other worlds out there"
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 763420.0,
      "end_time": 765818.0,
      "text": "and desperately wanting to know more about them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 767174.0,
      "end_time": 771108.0,
      "text": "wanting to interrogate them and find out if maybe just one or two of them"
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 771132.0,
      "end_time": 772742.0,
      "text": "are a little bit like you."
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 774244.0,
      "end_time": 776803.0,
      "text": "You can&#39;t do that. You can&#39;t go there, not yet."
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 776827.0,
      "end_time": 780820.0,
      "text": "And so you have to use the tools that you&#39;ve developed around you"
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 780844.0,
      "end_time": 782139.0,
      "text": "for Venus, Earth and Mars,"
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 782163.0,
      "end_time": 784976.0,
      "text": "and you have to apply them to these other situations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 785000.0,
      "end_time": 789696.0,
      "text": "and hope that you&#39;re making reasonable inferences from the data,"
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 789720.0,
      "end_time": 792838.0,
      "text": "and that you&#39;re going to be able to determine the best candidates"
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 792862.0,
      "end_time": 795261.0,
      "text": "for habitable planets, and those that are not."
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 796139.0,
      "end_time": 798854.0,
      "text": "In the end, and for now, at least,"
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 798878.0,
      "end_time": 801665.0,
      "text": "this is our red spot, right here."
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 802376.0,
      "end_time": 805712.0,
      "text": "This is the only planet that we know of that&#39;s habitable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 805736.0,
      "end_time": 808927.0,
      "text": "although very soon we may come to know of more."
    },
    {
      "index": 297,
      "start_time": 808951.0,
      "end_time": 811687.0,
      "text": "But for now, this is the only habitable planet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 298,
      "start_time": 811711.0,
      "end_time": 813130.0,
      "text": "and this is our red spot."
    },
    {
      "index": 299,
      "start_time": 813976.0,
      "end_time": 815396.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m really glad we&#39;re here."
    },
    {
      "index": 300,
      "start_time": 816507.0,
      "end_time": 817681.0,
      "text": "Thanks."
    },
    {
      "index": 301,
      "start_time": 817706.0,
      "end_time": 820937.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}